WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:21.710 --> 00:00:26.959
I see him here like Elisha,
like those Old Testament prophets

00:00:39.025 --> 00:00:44.040
He was sitting on the planks,
bound in chains.

00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:01.320
He had the power to expel
 evil spirits from people.

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:06.680
He is both holy and blessed.

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:22.800
At that time,
he was considered a prophet.

00:01:31.983 --> 00:01:35.394
Are you Jozo Furundžija? He
raises his head and says: Yes, I am.

00:01:38.568 --> 00:01:40.162
„ And why did you come to me?“

00:01:58.200 --> 00:02:05.019
When we decided to make
 a film about Jozo Furundžija

00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:10.480
I didn't yet know the Pougarian mentality

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:15.960
the resourcefulness and endurance
of a Pougarian man that well.

00:02:16.373 --> 00:02:19.914
But, shortly after I came
to Dobretići for the first time

00:02:20.026 --> 00:02:23.956
It was still summer
according to the calendar

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:28.800
It was September 20
and it snowed.

00:02:29.800 --> 00:02:33.566
We had to heat the car,
to heat the house where we slept

00:02:33.886 --> 00:02:40.957
I realized how beautiful, but also often harsh
 and inhospitable the Pougarian region was.

00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:44.600
Equally difficult was the history
 of the Pougarian people.

00:02:44.906 --> 00:02:47.906
This region has
always been spiritually rich.

00:02:50.080 --> 00:02:54.400
there were a lot of prayers, work
and a lot of faith.

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:57.080
Faith of these people is immense.

00:02:58.760 --> 00:03:03.640
Because if a Pougarian man did not
have faith, he could not survive here.

00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:09.073
They needed resourcefulness
and faithfulness to the Lord

00:03:09.113 --> 00:03:14.624
the Church and the friars who
preserved the faith to survive.

00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:21.240
Year that was a turning point
in the Bosnian Kingdom was 1463

00:03:21.240 --> 00:03:25.608
when Sultan Mehmed the
Conqueror conquered Bosnia.

00:03:34.463 --> 00:03:39.920
About 30,000 children and young people were
then taken as janissaries to Constantinople

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:47.000
Among them was the daughter of the
Bosnian nobleman Stjepan Dobreta, Ljiljana.

00:03:47.075 --> 00:03:53.480
Stjepan Dobreta had his estates  around
present-day Foča, southeastern Bosnia - southern Serbia

00:03:53.480 --> 00:03:56.595
Fleeing from the Sultan,
he ended up in today's Pougarje

00:03:56.625 --> 00:04:00.080
which was well-protected at an altitude
of 1200 meters above sea level.

00:04:00.626 --> 00:04:06.400
His daughter Ljiljana gained favor and entered
the harem as a noblewoman of Sultan El-Fatih,

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:08.700
she managed to obtain a land deed.

00:04:08.725 --> 00:04:16.640
It was a document in the Turkish Empire
confirming the ownership of the area between

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:21.663
the Ilomska River, Ugra River and
the old towns of Komotina and Knežnica

00:04:22.615 --> 00:04:25.200
belonging to her father,
Stjepan Dobreta.

00:04:25.401 --> 00:04:31.686
We could already see the resourcefulness
that would later characterize these people

00:04:31.872 --> 00:04:35.240
because during the Mehmed the Conqueror
the Pougarians, Catholics

00:04:35.265 --> 00:04:44.698
like Fra Anđeo Zvizdović, were given permission
to stay and became co-owners of the land.

00:04:45.356 --> 00:04:50.673
One interesting event is also
found in the writings and chronicles

00:04:50.766 --> 00:04:53.383
of the parish priest
Vladimir Matijašević from Korićani

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:58.794
who said when the Turkish
oppression became so intense

00:04:59.387 --> 00:05:03.954
one of those nobles and
descendants of Stjepan Dobrete

00:05:04.258 --> 00:05:09.359
Martin Baltić Dobretić
and Fra Stipan Margitić

00:05:09.407 --> 00:05:14.033
who is known for the standardization of the
national language and his famous Stipanuša

00:05:14.516 --> 00:05:18.384
They dared to go on foot
to Constantinople to meet

00:05:18.408 --> 00:05:22.954
with the Padishah Ahmed
III. and to remind him of the

00:05:23.047 --> 00:05:25.760
contract his ancestor
had concluded with their forefather.

00:05:26.273 --> 00:05:34.227
They traveled for two months, working along
the way to earn food, and reached Constantinople.

00:05:34.912 --> 00:05:41.468
When the Sultan was passing by,
 Martin Baltić thought of dressing up

00:05:41.493 --> 00:05:44.720
in Turkish attire and placed
four lighted candles on his head.

00:05:45.100 --> 00:05:51.156
He immediately stood out among
the crowd, and the Sultan noticed him.

00:05:51.534 --> 00:05:54.814
He managed to push his way through;
the guards brought him

00:05:54.839 --> 00:05:59.150
He knelt before the Sultan, kissed
his foot, and said he was coming from

00:05:59.175 --> 00:06:03.897
great distress to ask him to listen to him,
and the Sultan granted him an audience.

00:06:03.956 --> 00:06:10.732
He told him to come tommorow to the court,
where he would be admitted with his entourage.

00:06:11.664 --> 00:06:20.221
He explained to the Sultan the plight of the
Catholics in Pougarje but also reminded him that

00:06:20.246 --> 00:06:23.985
his great-grandfather Mehmed
the Conqueror gave that land deed to

00:06:24.010 --> 00:06:29.396
his great-grandfather Stjepan
Dobreta, which is no longer respected.

00:06:29.804 --> 00:06:34.777
Sultan swore before his whole entourage
that he would renew that land deed.

00:06:35.312 --> 00:06:38.636
However, Martin was not
satisfied with that solution.

00:06:38.962 --> 00:06:43.876
He told the Sultan that when he came before
the Judge of Jajce with that land deed

00:06:44.195 --> 00:06:49.860
he would have his head cut off and destroy
that land deed as physical evidence.

00:06:50.741 --> 00:06:53.894
The Sultan then asked him what he proposed.

00:06:55.332 --> 00:06:58.408
Martin suggested that the land
deed be tattooed on his back.

00:06:58.766 --> 00:07:00.771
Here, we see what resourcefulness that was.

00:07:01.214 --> 00:07:03.784
The Sultan agreed to this
even though he was surprised.

00:07:03.839 --> 00:07:07.748
The land deed was tattooed along
with his signature and seal on his back.

00:07:07.787 --> 00:07:10.897
When he came to Jajce,
he brought it in a paper form

00:07:10.992 --> 00:07:14.413
Then he took off his shirt and
showed it to the Judge of Jajce

00:07:14.437 --> 00:07:17.337
conveying warm greetings
from Sultan Ahmed III.

00:07:23.639 --> 00:07:29.702
Interesting fact for Pougarians that it is said:
 "Whoever seeks something here finds it."

00:07:32.297 --> 00:07:38.996
Pougarian man has always been
 reserved towards foreigners but also open.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:45.847
When a foreigner would come
and pass through a village;

00:07:46.601 --> 00:07:54.276
If it was night, people would invite him first
to have a drink and something to eat.

00:07:54.954 --> 00:07:57.806
Then if they saw he was okay,
they'd let him spend the night.

00:07:59.744 --> 00:08:03.672
If a stranger was looking for
bread here, he could always find it.

00:08:04.969 --> 00:08:08.250
If he was looking for a
beating, he could find that too.

00:08:08.591 --> 00:08:10.662
So, whoever asked for something got it.

00:08:10.905 --> 00:08:15.797
And it was a widespread occurrence
that the friars who would come to Pougarje,

00:08:15.896 --> 00:08:19.263
like in other parts of Bosnia, had
to pretend to be part of the family.

00:08:19.723 --> 00:08:22.884
That's why they were called
"uncles" so that when they came,

00:08:22.908 --> 00:08:26.060
the children wouldn't accidentally
reveal them to the Turks.

00:08:26.186 --> 00:08:32.579
They were dressed in clothes like other family members.
They even wore mustaches and often had red fez.

00:08:33.183 --> 00:08:40.753
Masses were held in the woods,
 which was easy to do in the summer months

00:08:40.778 --> 00:08:45.000
during those two or three summer months
 that summer lasted in Pougarje.

00:08:45.437 --> 00:08:54.846
However, in the winter, it often rained, snowed,
was cold, windy, and then they would put up planks.

00:08:55.329 --> 00:09:01.980
The priest would celebrate mass there. Above him,
they would hang goat skin so he wouldn't get wet.

00:09:02.458 --> 00:09:06.543
And it was so cold that
they kept stones in the fire

00:09:06.796 --> 00:09:11.387
Then wrapped those hot stones in
rags and put them in the priest's hands

00:09:11.427 --> 00:09:17.069
so that they wouldn't freeze so he could
perform the mass and turn the missal.

00:09:17.433 --> 00:09:21.733
All that time, the people were
wet, exposed to the wind, and cold

00:09:21.757 --> 00:09:26.456
Despite this, they tried to
celebrate the Holy Mass regularly.

00:09:26.740 --> 00:09:34.688
Thanks to that faith, that spirituality,
this region has a saint today.

00:09:54.841 --> 00:10:03.008
Jozo Furundžija was born on September 11, 1857, in the
Pougarje village of Gornji Orašac, Dobretići parish.

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:08.693
As it was customary at that time that an unbaptized
child could not spend the night in the house,

00:10:08.775 --> 00:10:11.044
he was immediately
baptized on the same day.

00:10:11.223 --> 00:10:15.496
He was baptized by Pavo Miličević, the parish
priest at the time in Pougarje, in Dobretići.

00:10:16.229 --> 00:10:18.054
Surname Furundžija is rare.

00:10:18.375 --> 00:10:24.951
His parents were Ivan and Mara Čulija.
They were peasants.

00:10:25.108 --> 00:10:30.421
The last name, Furundžija, is associated
with the "furine". Those were clay stoves.

00:10:30.929 --> 00:10:36.620
Jozo's father made such stoves, and Jozo was
named Furundžija after this type of craft.

00:10:37.243 --> 00:10:41.109
This is where Jozo's last name
comes from, after clay ovens ("furina").

00:10:41.668 --> 00:10:48.364
We don't know much about Jozo's life.
What is known is from parish books

00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:50.650
and the records kept by the
parish priests at the time.

00:10:51.288 --> 00:10:56.327
He lived in a tough time.
There was great poverty then.

00:10:56.352 --> 00:11:02.616
Bare survival only from farming and cattle
breeding. Only a few lived from a trade.

00:11:03.074 --> 00:11:07.098
Most was written about him by the then parish priest,
 the Franciscan Miroslav Džaja from Kupres.

00:11:07.861 --> 00:11:13.535
We know from his records
that Jozo was a weak student.

00:11:13.560 --> 00:11:16.523
In his youth, he was not
interested in anything.

00:11:16.696 --> 00:11:18.957
He was a big swearer.

00:11:20.508 --> 00:11:28.872
Not only did he insult God once. He invented
curses to insult God as much as possible.

00:11:29.764 --> 00:11:34.204
For example, he insulted God as many times
as there were blades of grass in the meadow.

00:11:35.381 --> 00:11:41.800
He liked to drink and liked fights and quarrels,
which were characteristic of all young people then.

00:12:17.819 --> 00:12:24.260
A member of our parish was
Jozo Furundžija, a reveler.

00:12:24.286 --> 00:12:29.575
I haven't found anywhere an
inscription saying someone was a reveler.

00:12:29.695 --> 00:12:38.140
For a while, he worked as an assistant to a priest
 and lived as a subtenant with an old woman.

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:42.953
Jozo decided not to marry and
he stuck to it until the end of his life.

00:12:43.241 --> 00:12:46.553
One Sunday he was at mass.

00:12:47.281 --> 00:12:53.546
He heard preaching, and it seemed to
him as if the priest was speaking directly to him.

00:12:54.125 --> 00:13:01.807
At that mass, parish priest said that Jesus
was stabbed in the side by some "londžija" (thug).

00:13:02.485 --> 00:13:08.287
He was always in his own little world
and didn't listen to anyone then.

00:13:08.662 --> 00:13:11.856
He understood that
Furundžija stabbed Jesus in the side.

00:13:13.067 --> 00:13:19.299
So Jozo ran out of the church and
 headed down to the villages of Pougarje.

00:13:20.056 --> 00:13:27.403
And he came to some rocks near the village
of Zapeće and wanted to end his life.

00:13:27.428 --> 00:13:35.043
He thought about how to do it, so he
decided to look for a rope and to hang himself.

00:14:15.578 --> 00:14:24.616
Then he had a vision where a young man, probably an angel, appeared to him and started to dissuade him from doing it.

00:14:24.982 --> 00:14:32.483
He dissuaded Jozo saying that he should
deter the people from evil, from suicide.

00:14:34.838 --> 00:14:39.956
Jozo obeyed this young man,
left the rope and went home.

00:14:40.403 --> 00:14:43.387
His house was in Orašac,
 the neighboring village of Zapeće.

00:14:44.158 --> 00:14:46.702
Since then, he has been
 at the service of the people.

00:15:34.660 --> 00:15:38.635
Jozo experienced his
 conversion similar to St. Paul.

00:15:39.165 --> 00:15:43.099
The sinful part of life and
 this mystical saintly part of life.

00:15:43.959 --> 00:15:51.102
Jozo's activity was here in three parishes:
Dobretići, Podmilačje and Jajce.

00:15:51.308 --> 00:15:57.500
From that moment, he decided to change
 his life and devote himself to God entirely.

00:15:58.024 --> 00:16:00.132
He began to mortify himself,
 to do penance.

00:16:00.448 --> 00:16:04.243
It is also known that Jozo ate bread
 that was sprinkled with ashes.

00:16:04.907 --> 00:16:11.992
He did not want to eat fresh bread,
but the older bread sprinkled with ashes.

00:16:12.405 --> 00:16:15.369
That's how he did his penance,
how he mortified himself.

00:16:15.704 --> 00:16:21.500
It is said that he always had
chains around him

00:16:21.651 --> 00:16:25.612
That he girded himself with chains,
 slept on the bare floor.

00:16:26.141 --> 00:16:30.275
That he often fasted and
 did other penance.

00:16:30.760 --> 00:16:36.131
He did penances in prayer,
various acts and chaining himself.

00:16:36.600 --> 00:16:40.532
Jozo, chained like that, went down on his knees
to the church in Podmilačje.

00:18:06.398 --> 00:18:12.266
The church was locked,
but after Jozo arrived there on his knees,

00:18:12.687 --> 00:18:16.699
It took him many days
on his knees bound with chains;

00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:23.869
The church doors opened for him by themselves
 and Jozo entered the church kneeling.

00:18:24.074 --> 00:18:29.409
I remember they talked about some
 thirty or forty kilometers he went

00:18:29.711 --> 00:18:32.205
He chose the most challenging route.

00:18:32.868 --> 00:18:39.284
Interesting thing and a good incentive
 for people who are converted

00:18:39.646 --> 00:18:45.790
Who pray a lot is that asceticism must lead
 to the apostolate, to serving people.

00:18:46.196 --> 00:18:54.921
There is a tradition that God clearly
showed Jozo through the ox that spoke

00:18:54.984 --> 00:19:01.643
That he shouldn't just pray for himself but engage
in the apostolate and proclaim this faith to others.

00:19:02.020 --> 00:19:06.863
This is a good example for
people today who understand prayer

00:19:06.903 --> 00:19:10.627
as something privately and
do not act evangelistically.

00:19:13.723 --> 00:19:17.691
Yes, there is that story about
the ox that Jozo once saw.

00:19:18.956 --> 00:19:23.186
He had gone outside
and returned to his room

00:19:23.616 --> 00:19:27.756
Then he had a vision of an ox
lying and chewing cud in his room.

00:19:28.543 --> 00:19:32.699
That ox said to Jozo: why are you
staring at me? What are you waiting for?

00:19:32.723 --> 00:19:37.507
Why are you lying down, not doing anything?
You are just like this ox chewing cud.

00:19:38.843 --> 00:19:43.497
This prompted Jozo towards
apostolate, and through this story,

00:19:43.525 --> 00:19:48.678
Jozo considered himself ordained for apostleship
and felt the need to preach the gospel further.

00:19:48.778 --> 00:19:55.952
When people came to ask him for advice,
 he would prophetically speak to them.

00:19:56.291 --> 00:19:57.716
This is my father's story

00:19:57.770 --> 00:20:02.591
He passed it on to me.
 I was named after my grandfather Matija

00:20:03.607 --> 00:20:10.961
Matija had a living testimony that
 he used to go to Jozo Furundžija.

00:20:12.227 --> 00:20:15.634
At that time,
 Jozo was considered a prophet

00:20:15.982 --> 00:20:21.740
When someone was in trouble, or
something undesirable happened

00:20:22.076 --> 00:20:26.749
They would seek advice
 and help from Jozo.

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:31.503
So, my grandfather lived at the
bottom of the village of Šimenice

00:20:32.524 --> 00:20:36.270
and his brother Stipan
lived at the top of the village.

00:20:38.208 --> 00:20:42.194
They were closely tied as a
family, inseparable brothers

00:20:42.553 --> 00:20:50.797
They always prayed together in the
evening, coming up or down to each other.

00:20:52.245 --> 00:20:57.437
As time went by, waiting for each other
 to come, neither came

00:20:57.616 --> 00:21:05.505
The evening prayer was not said regularly,
and livestock began to die slowly.

00:21:06.187 --> 00:21:10.476
Sheep died, goats died
 and calves died.

00:21:11.305 --> 00:21:18.574
And now the grandfather in
trouble didn't know what to do.

00:21:20.873 --> 00:21:28.055
And since Jozo always helped,
 he decided to go to Jozo.

00:21:29.564 --> 00:21:35.476
From Šibenica to Orašac
 is more than 30 km.

00:21:36.424 --> 00:21:43.340
There was no transportation and my
grandfather saddled the horse and went to Jozo.

00:21:44.407 --> 00:21:48.179
As he arrived in Orašac,
in front of the house

00:21:49.385 --> 00:21:54.261
Jozo from the house
called out: "Matija, come in."

00:21:55.622 --> 00:22:01.548
My grandfather was puzzled and stopped:
How does he know my name?

00:22:01.941 --> 00:22:04.862
"Come in, Matija;
I know why you came"

00:22:05.481 --> 00:22:08.744
"Your livestock is dying, your sheeps
are dying, your goats are dying."

00:22:10.226 --> 00:22:14.579
"It is because you don't
pray to God regularly"

00:22:14.707 --> 00:22:18.587
"You are at the bottom of the village
and your brother is at the top."

00:22:19.263 --> 00:22:23.723
"You are waiting for each other and
don't pray the regular evening prayer to God."

00:22:26.366 --> 00:22:32.521
Grandfather returned home and
they continued to follow what Jozo said:

00:22:33.524 --> 00:22:36.633
"Whoever is down in the house should pray,
 whoever is up there should pray"

00:22:36.681 --> 00:22:40.094
"Don't wait for each other,
you must pray regularly."

00:22:41.362 --> 00:22:48.797
As he returned, he told his brother that
and they obeyed what Jozo said

00:22:48.986 --> 00:22:54.748
And then the sacrifices stopped,
 the damages ceased.

00:22:54.974 --> 00:22:58.442
So, Jozo knew their situation exactly
and he didn't know any of them?

00:22:58.467 --> 00:22:59.624
That's right

00:22:59.648 --> 00:23:03.612
He had never seen my grandfather before,
nor had my grandfather been to him

00:23:04.443 --> 00:23:12.972
There is one event about my great-grandfather,
Ilija Aščić, who was supposed to have a baby.

00:23:13.836 --> 00:23:16.907
However, his wife couldn't give birth.

00:23:18.406 --> 00:23:25.998
They were persuading him to go to his
cousin Jozo for advice and some medicine.

00:23:26.894 --> 00:23:31.659
He said:"Why should I go to him?
 He knows like my mare."

00:23:34.440 --> 00:23:37.733
But his wife couldn't give birth;
the child wouldn't come out.

00:23:39.575 --> 00:23:43.859
And he broke down inside himself
and went to his cousin Jozo Furundžija

00:23:44.354 --> 00:23:48.275
When Jozo saw him,
he shouted from afar:

00:23:48.902 --> 00:23:53.201
"Cousin, why are you coming to me when
 even your mare knows better than I do?"

00:23:53.536 --> 00:23:58.710
He knew that, as God told him,
 he had "God's phone".

00:23:58.850 --> 00:24:02.498
Jozo said to him: "Go home;
 your wife will survive"

00:24:02.909 --> 00:24:07.071
"However, the bed will be bloody
 and the child will be dead."

00:24:07.461 --> 00:24:09.779
And that's what happened.

00:24:10.214 --> 00:24:14.251
His wife survived, but the child
that was to be born was stillborn.

00:24:15.015 --> 00:24:16.587
What kind of charisma did he have?

00:24:16.864 --> 00:24:20.260
Jozo had the power of bilocation
 to be in two places simultaneously.

00:24:20.784 --> 00:24:24.260
He knew how to move from the spiritual
 to the material world and vice versa.

00:24:24.574 --> 00:24:29.180
He managed to see what happened in the past
 and what would happen in the future.

00:24:29.790 --> 00:24:32.313
He had the gift of prophesying
 the thoughts of hearts.

00:24:32.500 --> 00:24:37.350
Jozo used all these gifts to serve people.
He probably had even more gifts.

00:24:37.443 --> 00:24:43.083
My mother-in-law had pneumonia
or inflammation in her lungs.

00:24:43.575 --> 00:24:51.150
Her mom went to Jozo Furundžija
and made a vow, and she went to Jozo.

00:24:59.329 --> 00:25:00.827
Jozo said to her:
"Aga"

00:25:02.288 --> 00:25:05.494
"She should eat snails for forty mornings"

00:25:06.123 --> 00:25:10.981
"She should take the snail out and
eat the bitter part."

00:25:14.753 --> 00:25:16.134
"Agata will recover."

00:25:16.769 --> 00:25:23.878
She had a cousin who
ate the snails with her.

00:25:31.062 --> 00:25:34.951
And my mother-in-law
recovered, and she told me about it.

00:25:35.742 --> 00:25:37.486
And she didn't have any
more problems afterward?

00:25:37.566 --> 00:25:38.322
No.

00:25:38.580 --> 00:25:44.202
My grandfather was born in 1898.

00:25:44.297 --> 00:25:48.979
He was 16 years old
before the First World War.

00:25:49.062 --> 00:25:52.158
He was sickly,
 he had some health problems

00:25:52.182 --> 00:26:00.054
and his parents took him
to Jozo regarding his health.

00:26:00.170 --> 00:26:05.588
Also, out of fear, because the
First World War was approaching,

00:26:05.612 --> 00:26:09.352
mobilizations were expected,
and they were afraid for their son.

00:26:09.383 --> 00:26:13.401
So they went to Jozo for a
prescription for his health and advice.

00:26:14.358 --> 00:26:17.903
And so Jozo helped them,
 regarding health,

00:26:18.042 --> 00:26:23.394
he gave grandfather some herbal tea,
which helped him, later he had no health issues.

00:26:23.435 --> 00:26:26.241
Regarding their fear
of mobilization, he said:

00:26:26.625 --> 00:26:30.795
"Don't worry, they will call
him, but he will return alive"

00:26:31.370 --> 00:26:33.399
he won't be in dangerous places.

00:26:33.938 --> 00:26:34.888
And was it like that?

00:26:34.955 --> 00:26:38.973
That's how it was, yes. Grandfather
lived, and they had fourteen children;

00:26:39.010 --> 00:26:40.980
He died at the age of 95.

00:26:47.805 --> 00:26:57.717
He it was who gave me sure knowledge of what exists, to understand the structure of the world and the action of the elements

00:27:00.396 --> 00:27:08.396
the beginning, end and middle of the times, the alternation of the solstices and the succession of the seasons

00:27:10.454 --> 00:27:18.831
the cycles of the year and the position of the stars; the natures of animals and the instincts of wild beasts

00:27:20.884 --> 00:27:27.659
the powers of spirits and human mental processes, the varieties of plants and the medical properties of roots.

00:27:29.211 --> 00:27:38.850
And now I understand everything, hidden or visible, for Wisdom, the designer of all things, has instructed me. Wisdom 7:17-21

00:27:38.883 --> 00:27:43.931
for Wisdom, the designer of all things, has instructed me.

00:27:51.843 --> 00:27:55.188
He had the power to expel
evil spirits from people.

00:27:55.639 --> 00:28:02.609
Jozo used that gift in his interactions with
people who came to him from other parishes:

00:28:02.648 --> 00:28:08.269
Podmilačje, Jajce, Dobretići, but also
from central Bosnia - Travnik.

00:28:08.422 --> 00:28:12.647
He was a worker and he worked for
Elektrobosna for 12 years.

00:28:12.686 --> 00:28:14.230
That's a company here in Jajce.

00:28:19.432 --> 00:28:24.690
Besides being a diligent worker and good
at all the jobs needed for the company.

00:28:25.382 --> 00:28:29.749
He also managed to influence
the workers and his colleagues

00:28:30.103 --> 00:28:32.446
Which is confirmed by
two stories from the book.

00:28:32.550 --> 00:28:35.940
These are the story about a malfunction
at Elektrobosna and a story about a wagon.

00:28:36.027 --> 00:28:38.198
What exactly happened with that malfunction?

00:28:38.272 --> 00:28:42.329
It was Saint John's Day, so
people needed to go to Mass

00:28:42.996 --> 00:28:46.371
and as they knew about
Jozo and Jozo's power

00:28:46.396 --> 00:28:52.549
they asked him to do something
so they could go to Mass.

00:28:52.598 --> 00:28:54.801
And Jozo promised to do something.

00:28:55.398 --> 00:29:00.390
Jozo prayed to God, and severe storms
happened, rainstorms and thunderstorms

00:29:00.414 --> 00:29:06.908
which led to the blockage of drains and canals
that prevented the company from working

00:29:06.932 --> 00:29:09.728
and then people of any confession
or religion could leave their jobs.

00:29:09.776 --> 00:29:12.945
Those who needed to go
to Mass could go to Mass.

00:29:13.315 --> 00:29:15.989
And the story about the wagon, what exactly is it about?

00:29:16.137 --> 00:29:18.518
The story is about one
wagon of Elektrobosna.

00:29:18.788 --> 00:29:24.948
The wagons were used to transport
ore and material for the company.

00:29:25.558 --> 00:29:31.209
That wagon couldn't move. Then
Jozo said he would do something

00:29:31.657 --> 00:29:34.201
He prayed and managed to start the wagon.

00:29:34.527 --> 00:29:40.388
He told that it was Satan himself who was under
the wagon that prevented the wagon from moving.

00:29:40.412 --> 00:29:44.462
Jozo was able to remove
that defect by praying.

00:29:44.487 --> 00:29:48.289
So, he testifies at his job?
Was he bold in proclaiming?

00:29:48.811 --> 00:29:53.056
Yes, just as he was up there in Pougarje,
he was the same  at work.

00:30:53.619 --> 00:30:54.772
He was dirty black.

00:30:55.480 --> 00:30:59.931
Children were out, he was leaving the
factory, and he was dirty black from work.

00:31:00.216 --> 00:31:04.770
He was going on foot;
there were no vehicles then.

00:31:07.485 --> 00:31:08.676
So children yelled to each other:

00:31:08.701 --> 00:31:10.858
"Come on, come out, come, see!"

00:31:10.883 --> 00:31:18.856
calling each other by name, "Come and see
this man who is coming, how ugly he is..."

00:31:19.216 --> 00:31:22.247
"Yes, I am, children, but even
the devil is afraid of me."

00:31:22.865 --> 00:31:26.021
After he converted,
people used to offend him:

00:31:26.045 --> 00:31:29.787
"Well, we know you, you have no right
to tell us anything, we know who you are."

00:31:29.830 --> 00:31:36.492
So, he used to insult God before, but
now he suffers and endures insults for God.

00:31:38.218 --> 00:31:41.612
They insulted him
until the end of his life.

00:31:42.083 --> 00:31:46.770
My grandmother got married
 very young, at 17

00:31:46.794 --> 00:31:50.188
She was married for four
years and didn't have children

00:31:50.838 --> 00:31:55.898
People from the village recommended
her to go to Jozo Furundžija

00:31:55.961 --> 00:32:00.545
as he was known for healing people and
 helping them, to see if he could help her.

00:32:00.883 --> 00:32:07.028
So she and her neighbor Ivka, who
also didn't have children, agreed to go.

00:32:07.727 --> 00:32:15.748
On the way to Jozo, as they traveled, they
talked about what each of them brought

00:32:15.780 --> 00:32:20.899
and my grandmother said: I knitted him
woolen socks and brought cheese and eggs.

00:32:21.313 --> 00:32:26.148
Ivka told her she had a mother-in-law, and
my grandmother didn't have a mother-in-law;

00:32:26.172 --> 00:32:29.441
she said: "My mother-in-law gave
me five eggs, and I was ashamed,

00:32:29.576 --> 00:32:33.558
so I took five more without askingher."
 And she also brought cheese.

00:32:34.226 --> 00:32:39.747
When they arrived, there was a
very long line of people in front

00:32:40.381 --> 00:32:42.683
They waited and
when it was their turn

00:32:42.794 --> 00:32:50.468
he was sitting on boards, chained,
and asked them why they had come.

00:32:51.202 --> 00:32:53.988
My grandma said: "I've
been married for four years

00:32:54.012 --> 00:32:56.709
I don't have children,
that it's hard for me."

00:32:56.995 --> 00:33:01.680
He looked at her and said: "Don't
worry; God will bless you with children."

00:33:02.355 --> 00:33:06.644
I think he told her she would
have four girls and eight boys.

00:33:07.596 --> 00:33:11.791
Jozo also told Ivka how
many children she would have.

00:33:12.282 --> 00:33:18.317
My grandmother gave him what
she had brought, and he thanked her.

00:33:18.341 --> 00:33:23.234
And Ivka did the same. However, he
took Ivka's eggs and sorted them out.

00:33:23.258 --> 00:33:26.411
They were surprised at what he was doing.

00:33:27.058 --> 00:33:32.114
He took five out of those ten,
returned them to Ivka and said:

00:33:32.139 --> 00:33:34.623
"You took these without
asking; give them back.

00:33:34.817 --> 00:33:38.561
And so, thank God my
grandmother returned to Bugojno.

00:33:38.585 --> 00:33:44.036
After a year, she gave birth to her
first son and continued to give birth.

00:33:58.411 --> 00:34:05.068
We decided to pray three Our Fathers or
another prayer, at will, for blessed Jozo

00:34:06.028 --> 00:34:11.628
Then he said: "Don't pray for me; pray
for my parents; my parents are not saved."

00:34:13.747 --> 00:34:15.196
That's what my mother-in-law told me.

00:34:15.634 --> 00:34:23.069
One man died from rakija (brandy);
He is from the same village as my mother-in-law.

00:34:23.474 --> 00:34:25.470
And his sons went to ask Jozo:

00:34:26.138 --> 00:34:30.910
"What would you do, Jozo? How
would you pray? Would you pay Masses?"

00:34:32.132 --> 00:34:36.038
Then he said: "He wasn't saved; he
died from alcohol; he died from brandy."

00:34:36.624 --> 00:34:40.911
So Jozo said that he was not saved and that
 there was no need to pray, then? - Yes.

00:34:41.819 --> 00:34:45.617
How did the clergy perceive it then?
Jozo Furundžija was a layman

00:34:46.188 --> 00:34:49.297
and now he begins to preach
the faith, and people come to him.

00:34:49.637 --> 00:34:54.605
Were the friars who were in
the parish then skeptical about it?

00:34:54.696 --> 00:34:57.886
How did they view the whole
phenomenon around Jozo?

00:34:57.918 --> 00:35:00.924
Especially considering the interest
of the people who were coming to him?

00:35:01.619 --> 00:35:08.395
Clergy viewed it with contempt,
 maybe with silence and some rejection

00:35:08.513 --> 00:35:12.689
They were not interested in
Jozo or what Jozo was doing at all.

00:35:14.176 --> 00:35:18.718
That is still the case today. If someone
rises above the ordinary, the average.

00:35:18.901 --> 00:35:25.092
Then he either falls into trouble,
into silence or has conflicts.

00:35:25.416 --> 00:35:31.890
As the Holy Scripture says, Jesus had the most problems with the priests, scribes, and the Pharisees.

00:35:32.798 --> 00:35:38.427
Jozo often had problems with the
friars who served here in this parish.

00:35:39.205 --> 00:35:44.756
The friars didn't quite agree with
his way of life and his teachings.

00:35:45.328 --> 00:35:50.146
It's difficult for us to accept
another teaching, another spirituality.

00:35:50.969 --> 00:35:57.443
And Jozo had his spirituality, his teachings;
 he had his life of penance.

00:35:58.079 --> 00:36:04.137
If they forbid Jozo from doing
that, if they hindered him in his plan

00:36:04.422 --> 00:36:06.724
Then they would be making
Jozo an advertisement

00:36:06.867 --> 00:36:09.970
and that would cause people
to pray and convert even more.

00:36:10.137 --> 00:36:13.068
So people were going to Jozo when he was
alive, but also to his grave

00:36:13.241 --> 00:36:16.133
because Jozo said that he
would help them, alive and dead.

00:36:38.767 --> 00:36:42.411
The child was healthy; he
spoke typically for his age.

00:36:42.455 --> 00:36:55.310
He went to the spring for water, and
Jozo's mare was grazing near the spring.

00:36:56.981 --> 00:37:04.548
He came near the mare and she hit him in
the chest. As she hit him, she threw him.

00:37:06.785 --> 00:37:15.060
And he lost his breath;
he could not speak at all.

00:37:15.552 --> 00:37:19.131
Suddenly, I was struck dumb;
I came home unable to speak,

00:37:19.646 --> 00:37:25.388
My mother and father promised
to carry me to Jozo's grave.

00:37:25.537 --> 00:37:28.959
They did that for three years;
they carried me up to Jozo's grave.

00:37:29.152 --> 00:37:33.147
We didn't go to a doctor but
straight to Saint John in Podmilačje.

00:37:34.258 --> 00:37:44.147
From Saint John to Saint Anthony in Pougarje,
 from Saint Anthony to Jozo's grave.

00:37:44.671 --> 00:37:49.969
Well, I can only remember
 that I was little then.

00:37:50.010 --> 00:37:56.260
Then, when we came to Jozo's
grave for the third time, we prayed there

00:37:56.836 --> 00:38:06.987
Fulfilled our vow, walked around the grave,
took the child and started walking home.

00:38:07.042 --> 00:38:17.033
I remember the pilgrimage to Jozo Furundžija's
 place that I experienced and got well.

00:38:20.979 --> 00:38:27.440
The child started to speak
as if nothing happened;

00:38:27.696 --> 00:38:33.388
he had no idea that something had
gone wrong; everything was as it should be.

00:38:33.510 --> 00:38:35.052
My mother told me:

00:38:35.259 --> 00:38:40.882
"Ivica, you went to Jozo's grave and
couldn't speak and now you can even yap."

00:38:41.135 --> 00:38:43.045
I said: "I know, mother."

00:38:44.497 --> 00:38:50.148
He was interested in politics and was not apolitical at all.
We can see that he was a genuinely engaged lay faithful.

00:38:50.696 --> 00:38:56.741
I read in the book about his involvement
in the 1910 elections in Pougarje.

00:38:57.114 --> 00:39:02.385
He took a side and was quite
fierce and passionate about that issue

00:39:03.100 --> 00:39:10.733
Yes, 1910 was an election year, and the
Croats were then divided into two parties

00:39:11.153 --> 00:39:16.788
Similar to today, when there are elections or
no elections, the Croats are always divided.

00:39:17.447 --> 00:39:22.993
One party was the Croatian Catholic Association,
and the other was the Croatian Community.

00:39:23.617 --> 00:39:32.425
Jozo Furundžija was a fervent supporter of association led by the auxiliary bishop of Sarajevo, Šarić

00:39:32.965 --> 00:39:38.295
The Croatian community was led by a prominent
Sarajevo lawyer, legal expert Dr. Jozo Sunarić.

00:39:39.143 --> 00:39:45.668
And thanks to Jozo's merit and influence,
the association got more votes in Dobretići

00:39:45.922 --> 00:39:52.569
than this community represented by the parish
priest and neighboring priests and clergymen.

00:39:52.703 --> 00:39:56.708
My mother vowed to go
to Jozo Furunđija's grave

00:39:56.732 --> 00:40:02.313
because I had huge problems
with my teeth when I was little.

00:40:02.956 --> 00:40:06.908
There were also situations
when I would lose consciousness

00:40:07.670 --> 00:40:12.246
So we can say that it is a mercy
that it stopped, and I felt better.

00:40:12.604 --> 00:40:20.035
The story about this, I would say, unusual man
 was present in our family, in our village.

00:40:20.080 --> 00:40:25.660
I'm from Mijatovići, a
neighboring village to Orašac

00:40:25.707 --> 00:40:30.024
where Jozo Furundžija
lived and was later buried.

00:40:30.459 --> 00:40:35.268
These stories were an integral part
of almost everyday conversations.

00:40:35.665 --> 00:40:38.127
They were talked about and discussed.

00:40:38.175 --> 00:40:44.485
These were not just ordinary tales
and stories retold over coffee or as a joke

00:40:44.564 --> 00:40:56.007
These were instructive severe stories with a certain
catechetical aim, some sort of folk catechesis.

00:40:56.381 --> 00:41:00.843
To teach the people of that
time, especially young people

00:41:01.215 --> 00:41:09.119
That by emulating this example, they try to
nurture those Christian values in their lives.

00:41:09.441 --> 00:41:13.726
Of course, a lot of what people had written
about Jozo was destroyed by this unfortunate war.

00:41:14.623 --> 00:41:20.440
According to the stories that reached me
and are certainly known to the wider public,

00:41:20.481 --> 00:41:25.504
especially to the people in
Pougarje, Jajce, and Travnik

00:41:25.818 --> 00:41:33.464
some special things were happening,
we can freely say even some miraculous acts

00:41:33.511 --> 00:41:36.307
precisely through the intercession
of this extraordinary man.

00:41:36.834 --> 00:41:47.475
My sister was quite sick during
the first three years of her life.

00:41:48.681 --> 00:41:54.327
Mom said that if she was well for
two weeks, the third week she wasn't

00:41:54.469 --> 00:41:59.240
The third week, she always had to go for
injections, and that was ongoing for three years.

00:41:59.999 --> 00:42:05.202
Mom had already lost hope
that the child would ever get well

00:42:06.153 --> 00:42:14.530
Then one woman from
the village advised her:

00:42:14.999 --> 00:42:18.440
"Why don't you take her
 to Jozo's grave?"

00:42:18.992 --> 00:42:24.769
Then, mom started carrying
her there a few times

00:42:24.793 --> 00:42:30.630
and her health improved,
and to this day, she's okay.

00:42:30.963 --> 00:42:34.840
I was at Jozo Furundžija's
grave; whatever illness finds me

00:42:35.218 --> 00:42:42.868
I promise to go to Furundžija's grave. I
went barefoot and in shoes; it's far to walk.

00:42:43.526 --> 00:42:49.410
God always helped me and blessed
Jozo Furundžija; I always got well.

00:42:49.434 --> 00:42:53.997
My back was hurting, and I
had all sorts of health problems.

00:42:54.080 --> 00:42:59.238
Whatever happens to me, as soon as
I leave the cemetery, that wish of mine comes true.

00:42:59.566 --> 00:43:03.169
So you also had problems
with bleeding for a long time?

00:43:04.528 --> 00:43:07.450
Yes, I was in the hospital.

00:43:07.532 --> 00:43:11.268
And as soon as I went to Furundžija's
grave, I felt better immediately.

00:43:12.029 --> 00:43:17.268
So dear God and Jozo healed me,
and I'm fine. I don't know about others.

00:43:17.879 --> 00:43:24.253
I believe in God and Jozo. I say there's
no better for me than at Jozo Furundžija's.

00:43:24.820 --> 00:43:34.833
Before I even thought about it,
I found out that my daughter had a tumor.

00:43:35.012 --> 00:43:41.837
When I was 22 or 23 years old, I started
feeling some pain in my stomach and the pelvis

00:43:42.114 --> 00:43:48.068
I ignored it, took some pills,
and so on until I fainted once.

00:43:48.759 --> 00:43:58.468
Then I went to the doctor. They sent me to
a surgeon, then to an internist and a urologist

00:43:58.738 --> 00:44:04.108
for various examinations
until finally to a gynecologist

00:44:04.132 --> 00:44:07.942
who told me I had a
tumor the size of an orange.

00:44:08.841 --> 00:44:15.828
From the beginning, I pretended
as if it wasn't happening to her

00:44:16.531 --> 00:44:19.132
it couldn't be, she's young.

00:44:21.659 --> 00:44:25.508
Then, it got even worse; I
fell into depression and fear.

00:44:26.198 --> 00:44:31.717
I remember at that time, the only thing I was sorry
for was that I was going to die and I had no children.

00:44:31.764 --> 00:44:40.140
My wife's uncle collected money for the construction
of a chapel near Jozo Furundžija's grave.

00:44:40.624 --> 00:44:47.548
I said, let's trust in God and the prayer of
Jozo that she will get well and be fine.

00:44:48.349 --> 00:44:50.014
And we gave that money.

00:44:50.892 --> 00:44:55.321
I didn't even know that my dad
had given money for the chapel

00:44:55.917 --> 00:45:02.589
When I did a tumor marker test, it was
perfectly fine, meaning a normal result.

00:45:03.332 --> 00:45:09.739
She said that day, she
didn't know I had given money

00:45:09.763 --> 00:45:14.819
that she felt a strange reaction in
her body, that it was indescribable.

00:45:15.604 --> 00:45:20.501
She couldn't describe what
was happening to her body

00:45:21.128 --> 00:45:27.784
Then, upon the next blood
test, the result was negative.

00:45:28.397 --> 00:45:33.348
I went to Jozo's grave with my mom
when I was little, maybe 2-3 years old.

00:45:34.221 --> 00:45:41.268
But before that, mom took my brother
Mijo there because he couldn't walk.

00:45:41.776 --> 00:45:46.593
She made a vow and went
to Jozo Furundžija's grave.

00:45:49.656 --> 00:45:55.256
When she returned from Jozo's grave from
Orašac, my brother Mijo started walking.

00:45:56.201 --> 00:46:01.942
During the war, we fled, and I went
as a refugee to Germany to work

00:46:02.049 --> 00:46:07.483
I worked in Berlin with my
father, mother, brother, and sister.

00:46:07.722 --> 00:46:14.265
I worked there, and after a while, I had
a headache every Saturday and Sunday.

00:46:15.270 --> 00:46:20.215
I was practically dying
from those headaches

00:46:20.893 --> 00:46:25.030
Only a pill could help me a little.

00:46:26.045 --> 00:46:31.986
And it was like that all the time, all
Saturdays, Sundays. And then I came back.

00:46:32.431 --> 00:46:34.434
How long did those headaches last?

00:46:34.498 --> 00:46:38.311
That lasted for three years,
as long as I was in Berlin.

00:46:38.648 --> 00:46:43.219
When I returned to Tomislavgrad in 1996

00:46:45.727 --> 00:46:48.906
I went to Jozo Furundžija's grave

00:46:50.239 --> 00:46:59.268
I laid down on his grave; after that, when
I returned home, my headache was gone.

00:47:00.775 --> 00:47:03.177
I never had a headache again.

00:47:04.446 --> 00:47:11.148
I realized I was fine, and after that, I
raised a monument to Jozo Furundžija.

00:47:11.267 --> 00:47:18.512
I raised a statue and mosaic
tiles in honor of Jozo Furundžija.

00:47:18.860 --> 00:47:23.222
My son was sick; his ears
hurt; they were leaking.

00:47:23.591 --> 00:47:27.655
I took him to the doctor; she
said he needed ten injections.

00:47:27.845 --> 00:47:34.745
He was okay for a month, and then
again, the doctor and ten injections.

00:47:35.256 --> 00:47:40.987
And it was going like
that for several times.

00:47:41.105 --> 00:47:43.185
When his ears started
leaking for the third time

00:47:43.258 --> 00:47:46.569
I looked at my child
and felt sorry for him.

00:47:46.974 --> 00:47:52.910
I thought, why wouldn't I
take my child to blessed Jozo?

00:47:53.829 --> 00:47:57.853
In the morning, my child woke up; nothing
was leaking, and it never did again.

00:47:57.957 --> 00:48:02.188
When the first Tuesday came,
I took him to Jozo's grave.

00:48:03.228 --> 00:48:09.215
And so, my child recovered, thank God. Today,
he is 35 years old, healthy, young, and works.

00:48:09.538 --> 00:48:11.948
So many people come to his grave.

00:48:13.023 --> 00:48:15.167
So many people pray at his grave.

00:48:16.032 --> 00:48:23.553
So many people testify that through his
intercession, they received hearings from God.

00:48:24.625 --> 00:48:30.743
I believe that is enough testimony
that he entered God's calendar as a saint.

00:48:30.845 --> 00:48:33.728
There are many such stories

00:48:33.821 --> 00:48:39.273
many people have healed through the
intercession and help of Jozo Furundžija.

00:48:39.865 --> 00:48:46.305
Many of these stories, events, and healing
 experiences have not been written down.

00:48:46.369 --> 00:48:53.316
I have only collected a little and put it in
the book, and this book is just "the first cry."

00:49:27.568 --> 00:49:29.711
He is both holy and blessed.

00:49:37.384 --> 00:49:40.265
Jozo Furundžija was a great saint to me.

00:49:47.708 --> 00:49:51.224
When she went again,
they told her the tumor was gone.

00:50:01.583 --> 00:50:03.901
Why don't you take her to Jozo's grave?

00:50:12.717 --> 00:50:15.448
Why wouldn't I take my child to blessed Jozo?

00:50:26.336 --> 00:50:27.717
moja svekrva ozdravila

00:50:36.610 --> 00:50:37.792
This region has a saint.

00:50:43.252 --> 00:50:48.132
When Jozo died, they packed the chains
 with him and buried them in his coffin.

00:50:48.478 --> 00:50:52.968
The parish priest up in Pougarje
 put the chains on his tombstone.

00:50:53.029 --> 00:50:58.392
This year, the centenary of the death of this
folk saint, Jozo Furundžija, was celebrated.

00:50:58.798 --> 00:51:01.424
Namely, Jozo died in 1922.

00:51:02.263 --> 00:51:05.125
The mass was held at
Orašac this year on July 29

00:51:05.633 --> 00:51:12.193
There were many believers, as you could
see in the report on Herceg Bosna television.

00:51:28.556 --> 00:51:32.699
I read in the book that Jozo
requested his grave to be excavated

00:51:32.746 --> 00:51:37.766
after 30 years to see
the condition of his body.

00:51:42.701 --> 00:51:47.567
"Thirty years after my death, dig me
up, and you will see what form I am in."

00:51:48.328 --> 00:51:55.105
Jozo wanted to emphasize that he wasn't a
fraud in life, nor won't be in death either.

00:52:08.750 --> 00:52:10.877
You said there were over 1,000 people?

00:52:11.921 --> 00:52:17.425
Well, someone says a 1000 or
a 1500 people; there were many people.

00:52:17.449 --> 00:52:21.021
I think this area here has
never seen anything like that.

00:52:21.046 --> 00:52:26.228
Jozo didn't make a distinction between people.
He helped both Orthodox Christians and Muslims

00:52:26.252 --> 00:52:30.708
That's why his way of life and
his message are relevant today.

00:52:30.765 --> 00:52:35.348
I saw that there were Muslims
and Orthodox Christians.

00:52:35.760 --> 00:52:41.918
They heard about that celebration, they were well
informed and managed to set aside that one day,

00:52:41.965 --> 00:52:44.920
so they came to Jozo's
grave and prayed to Jozo.

00:52:47.350 --> 00:52:52.108
One of the criteria in the beatification process
is the sensus fidei, the sense in the people.

00:52:52.441 --> 00:53:00.291
As a parish priest here, can you notice that the veneration
of Jozo and the word about Jozo are growing increasingly?

00:53:00.528 --> 00:53:07.578
Yes. Since my childhood, more and more people have been going to Jozo's grave, especially on Tuesdays.

00:53:07.686 --> 00:53:10.102
It's a bit of a paradox.

00:53:10.506 --> 00:53:16.148
It may sound harsh, but thanks
to a dead man, life is born.

00:53:16.553 --> 00:53:23.605
Thanks to his noble deeds that remained and
couldn't die.

00:53:23.811 --> 00:53:27.055
Beautiful things arise now.
New things are born

00:53:27.221 --> 00:53:34.226
Sometimes, we living people cannot do what the
deeds of some people who lived before us can.

00:53:34.338 --> 00:53:40.166
In many ways, he is a luminous figure for this time. I hope
that God's providence has led us to this just at this time

00:53:40.634 --> 00:53:44.474
when many Catholics live
trapped in swearing and alcohol

00:53:44.815 --> 00:53:54.622
when many lay people should engage in apostolate and be
active in politics, witnessing at work, and promoting peace.

00:53:54.844 --> 00:53:58.172
These are all qualities that Jozo had

00:53:58.679 --> 00:54:05.715
Karl Rahner says that in the 21st century, Catholics
will either become mystics or not be at all.

00:54:05.739 --> 00:54:09.663
Jozo is a shining example
of that mystical life.

00:54:10.195 --> 00:54:14.478
We can say that nowadays,
he is very relevant.

00:54:14.882 --> 00:54:22.666
What is your prediction? Since you may have dealt with
this bright figure the most, when will the process start?

00:54:22.959 --> 00:54:26.708
The process of beatification
is a long process.

00:54:29.247 --> 00:54:35.886
A process that requires sure evidence.
For now, we have people's testimonies.

00:54:36.623 --> 00:54:44.228
Some testimonies are also written, and we also
have some legends and stories that people tell.

00:54:45.014 --> 00:54:49.867
Now, the official church
needs to initiate it.

00:54:50.082 --> 00:54:56.680
For me, it was surprising after the war to
see how people did not return to their homes

00:54:56.720 --> 00:54:59.632
few have returned, but they
return to Jozo Furundžija.

00:55:57.633 --> 00:56:02.192
"Blessed" Jozo, prays for us!

00:56:02.380 --> 00:56:22.652
Prayer to Jozo Furundžija
Dear God, grant us the health of soul and body through
 the intercession of our "blessed" Joz‭o. May his conversion 
and great sacrifice to you encourage us to walk bravely
 through our lives, preserve the health of soul and body, 
serve you all our lives, and always humbly pray and turn to 
you in all our life's needs. May the intercession of our 
"blessed" Jozo always accompany us through life,  on all 
our paths, in our work, and our homes. Help us to be better
 people and Christians, to love Christ more, and to serve
 His Church and our brethren. May his living faith always 
help us in all our life's struggles until our eternal salvation. 
Amen.

